this pak's balancing is screwed up
by that, i mean the base speeds
I actually think the issue is map size... whereas some base speed/bonus work on  a small map, they can be ridiculious on a larger map
I've done a lot of research into the speedbonus. the problem is that it acts mostly like a speed penalty
most of the time, you haul below the bonus speed and incur a penalty
so for high-speedbonus goods, you have to lower runnig cost of things
true.. speedbonus tendfs to be very close or ahead of the fastest vehicles available
but low/no speedbonus goods incur no penalty and thus make $$$
by drastically droping base speeds and rebalancing accordingly, this problem can be eliminated
if you look at freight toward the end of a game, high speedbounus goods barely make a profit and stuff like bulk brings in the money
because you're hauling it with, say max 200 trains
I have barely taken a game to 2100 yet, but I can see that happening
speedbouns stops changing after 2030 or so
but the effective power of a train at 200 kmh is considerably less than at 120
so you get more than intended power without a correspondingly high cost because bonus speeds are so high
its comcastic!
